WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:17.340
Alright, in this module we're going to talk about how we can also connect devices together

00:17.340 --> 00:35.320
by using wireless technologies, but alright, in this module we're going to talk about how

00:35.320 --> 00:40.720
we can also connect devices together by using wireless technologies, but one of the things

00:40.720 --> 00:46.480
that we have to think about in anything wireless is that we can't really control how we

00:46.480 --> 00:52.960
connect devices together because by definition wireless signals will span outwards in all directions

00:52.960 --> 00:59.840
and so that makes it particularly challenging to protect anything that is wireless and

00:59.840 --> 01:05.240
you know up until a number of years ago this was something that companies resisted simply

01:05.240 --> 01:11.600
because it was so hard to protect wireless communications, but nowadays we can protect

01:11.600 --> 01:16.640
