03:18.440 --> 03:23.560
the firewall to be able to access anything of value in the internal network, now you could

03:23.560 --> 03:30.520
have a guest Wi-Fi so this is a typical architecture that a lot of organizations have, this is where

03:30.520 --> 03:37.080
you would place your Wi-Fi capabilities that you offer guests which could be on the outside

03:37.080 --> 03:43.640
and not in any way connected to the internal network which again is the most important thing

03:43.640 --> 03:50.040
to protect, the value of the internal network and its services is what we want to ultimately protect,

03:50.040 --> 03:56.280
so your guest Wi-Fi capabilities are going to be outside of the firewall, now you could also have

03:56.280 --> 04:03.800
what most companies do and that is a corporate Wi-Fi that only authorized individuals are allowed

04:03.800 --> 04:09.960
