04:09.960 --> 04:16.600
but probably two factor authentication for anyone that may be a employee of the organization

04:16.600 --> 04:23.560
to connect to that type of network, now one of the other things that we have to think about

04:24.520 --> 04:31.000
from a wireless perspective is what we call radio frequency management and what this means is that

04:31.000 --> 04:39.000
the placement of certain wireless access points need to be done securely and what you depict here,

04:39.000 --> 04:45.640
what you see here is not very secure because we've placed a wireless access point in the corner

04:45.640 --> 04:54.520
